post_text:
To the ROWVA CUSD 208 Community

Since April, the administration and Future Ready team have been working hard to prepare for the upcoming school year. Although this is the case, there are still a few items that are not in place that I feel are vital to opening safely. In order to give these items time to arrive, we will be utilizing two more of our allotted remote learning preparation days to start the school year. These will count as attendance days, so we will not be making them up at the end of the year. Our first day of student attendance will now be Monday, August 24th.

I apologize for the inconvenience this causes everyone, but I want to make sure that all of our safety precautions are in place before we bring our students back into the building. If you have any questions, please contact the district office 309-483-3711 with concerns.

Sincerely,
Superintendent Sornberger

Traci Johnson
July 16 at 11:09 AM ¬∑

Dear #rowvastrong parents, I just want to take a minute to say THANK YOU for the support you give the teachers of ROWVA. I've been reading some pretty nasty stuff from parents of other districts, but I have felt nothing but support from the ROWVA community. I know this is hard. I know we all want it to be over. But in the in-between time, I'm going to do my best to educate your children whether we are at home or in person. And I feel that each parent knows that and has my back. It's a pretty good day to be a Tiger. Thank you ROWVA. Today, and every day. Together we'll get through this and come out stronger on the other side.

*Please feel free to share. I don't have all my students' parents on here, and I'd love for them to know how grateful I am.

post_text:
For the first-time since Family, Career and Community Leaders of America (FCCLA) was founded in 1945, members competed in Students Taking Action with Recognition (STAR) Events on the national level virtually.

ROWVA Students competed at the Section and State level before being chosen to compete at the national level. Madison Walker and Brenna West earned a Bronze rating in Level 3 Chapter in Review Display. Taryn Henry received a Gold rating in Level 3 Say Yes to FCS. Alexis McKeag and Annalyn Lovell earned a Gold rating in FCCLA Chapter Website Level 3. Congratulations!

There are six ROWVA Students who are attending the Virtual Conference: Gracie Gibbons, Taryn Henry, Madison Walker, Brenna West, Alexis McKeag, and Annalyn Lovell as well as their adviser Mrs. Neill-Nelson. #rowvastrong

post_text:
Just as we have been carefully making a new remote learning plan, taking stakeholders opinions into account, we will do the same with the new guidelines that came out yesterday. There are two transition teams, elementary and 7-12, made up of teachers and administrators. They plan to go over all data and finalize the remote learning plan today.

Then, they will begin to tackle the large undertaking of figuring out how we can meet the guidelines while doing what we all believe is best for our students. They will probably take a few days to research and process the 60 page document before beginning to formulate the next survey to parents and students. Thank you for your patience as we work to create plans. We will be reaching out for more opinions as we continue. It will take all of us to make this happen! Together, we are #rowvastrong

Section 4 FFA
May 5 at 2:00 PM ¬∑

The 2019-20 school year has been different, to say the least. During FFA's busiest season, we have been advised to stay home. Many contests, elections, and banquets have been postponed, canceled, or are being held virtually.
During this time, the Section 4 officer team would like to thank those that have led their chapters through this unpredictable year. Seniors, we wish you the best of luck in your future endeavors. Thank you all for your commitment to FFA this year.

That wraps up Signing Day 2020, but it is only the beginning of our celebration for our seniors. Please check back for more pictures, videos, and announcements about the Class of 2020 as the month of May continues.

Seniors, while the last leg of your K-12 journey was not what you expected, we know you will take the next step with courage and strength. We hope that you have learned what you need from your time here at ROWVA to make you feel prepared for the exciting journey ahead! #rowvastrong #BetterMakeRoom #CollegeSigningDay

post_text:
Upward Bound/UBMS updates:
Hello, parents and students!
The TRIO Upward Bound and Upward Bound Math-Science college readiness programs have extended our application deadline to May 15!
We have also created a new, online application: bit.ly/TRIO-UB-UBMS-Application

Simply click on the link above, which will allow you to more easily complete and submit the application. After you submit the application, we will contact you to schedule a remote interview! As always, we are very grateful for your continued interested in their TRIO Upward Bound and Upward Bound Math-Science programs, and we appreciate your patience as we worked to recreate our application processes. We look forward to receiving your application!

Our students are among the most successful in Knox County in finding, getting into, and graduation from college. Don‚Äôt miss out on this unique opportunity!

post_text: Join ROWVA HS & other high schools with #BeTheLight campaign to show our support for our Senior Class of 2020! This Friday, April 17th, we will light up the Bill Adams Field from 8:00 pm-8:20 pm. We invite every home to turn their outside lights on during this time to help us "light up" the ROWVA community in support of our seniors! Feel free to drive by and honk as teachers and coaches will be lined in their cars at the north end of the field. Please honor social distancing and stay in your vehicles. Together, we are #rowvastrong.

Julie Lake Storm
March 25 at 5:36 PM ¬∑

I wanted to remind everyone that we are still distributing lunches in the ROWVA School District. This is a hard time for everyone with businesses closing. Many have been laid off or lost their jobs. These lunches are available for ALL of our children. If you would like to add your child/children to the list, email Principal Danner at kdanner@rowva.k12.il.us or you can also email me at jstorm@rowva.k12.il.us. Lunches are distributed each day (M-F) at 12 pm across from the post office in all of our towns. Practice social distancing when picking up your lunches! Stay safe.‚ù§

More Than Sad Parent Presentation

Parents, teachers and community members can learn about detecting when a youth is dealing with depression or other mental illnesses.

Regional Office of Education 33 is offering parents and community members the presentation tonight, Tuesday, January 28 from 6:00 to 7:00 p.m. at the Thomas Legacy Center on Seminary Street.
